{
  "stem": "26142.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- and-- the Hasidic community has a-- a-- special-- special trait, that-- that they are celebrating everything in a-- in a happy mood.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Everything was in a joyful, in a joyful mood.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So those were-- those were the-- the-- the Shabbats, Friday night.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And-- and especially very-- very often, rabbis used to come.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Famous rabbis used to come visit those small communities.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I'm not talking about rabbis the way we understand them here-- rabbis that are-- are-- are paid-- paid by communities.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I'm talking about rabbis that had followers in the thousands.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I mean, famous rabbis.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They were not a rabbi-- rabbi from Allentown or-- they were [INAUDIBLE]-- they-- they were-- by-- first of all, most-- most of them had-- had to have published some-- some writings about Torah.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And-- and some of them were called by their names-- the names of the-- of the commentaries that they had written.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So-- and another thing-- the Baal Shem movement-- the Hasidic movement-- they believed that some of the people, some of these rabbis are capable of-- of performing miracles.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And people believed in that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "To get a bracha-- you know what a bracha is?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A blessing from a rabbi, it was worth a lot-- a lot of money.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- and people believed in that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and so a lot of them used to come.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I-- I speak about this here, because since we had a big-- a big house, and we had enough room, they used to stay-- most-- most of the time, they used to stay in our house.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they would stay for a-- for almost a week.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
